tweet: 8/9 By limiting travel and face-to-face contact now, we reduce the potential to overwhelm our rural healthcare facilities and cause unnecessary deaths ahead. Wyoming’s rural nature does not protect us from impacts.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 7/9 Like the rest of America, Wyoming’s access to testing supplies is limited. Our best tool right now for slowing the spread of this disease is practicing social distancing measures.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 6/9 ...the enormity of the public health challenge facing us and respond to it. COVID-19 may seem far away, but it is here. Our neighboring states are all experiencing the same escalation in the number of positive cases as we are.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 5/9 I am a businessman and understand full well what the consequences would be of closures. I know that the worst impacts would fall on those least able to absorb it.   As confirmed cases have grown from 1 to 23 in a week, spanning 8 counties, we should be honest about...

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 4/9 ...that unemployment benefits are readily accessible, that those who are food insecure are fed, and that our essential business functions are preserved. I am proud of my Wyoming heritage and the fact that we can serve as a beacon for our nation.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 3/9 We are in this for the long haul and we will emerge stronger for this test, and I will always be guided by my concern for the health and safety of the people of Wyoming. folks at the state are working 24/7 to assure that proper supplies arrive as quickly as possible...

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 2/9 From the beginning, I have emphasized that the challenge we are facing represents two threats: disease and economic harm.  I have been very clear that both are important.  I believe firmly we must do the right thing, do it right away, and do it the right way.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: 1/9 The coronavirus is the most disruptive thing that most of us have ever seen.  I recognize and appreciate the criticism from some that we have not acted rapidly, and I appreciate and recognize the criticism that we have acted too much. #COVID19WY

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: The ports of the United States of America are for all the commerce of the United States of America. We stand today to ensure reasonable access to that foreign trade for all of Wyoming’s and Montana’s products and those of the other states without access to ports.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: A de facto blockade limiting the citizens of any state to participate in interstate and international commerce cannot be arbitrarily imposed by another. Congress has the sole authority to regulate trade.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: This is an effort to protect all the rights of states as guaranteed under the Constitution -- all rights including those that pertain to commerce.  It is neither a political battle nor an attempt to ride roughshod over the legitimate rights of states to manage their own affairs

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: Our Constitution was written to ensure that interior states have access to foreign markets through our coastal sister states. Today we are defending Wyoming’s and Montana’s right to utilize American port and rail infrastructure for its products.

name: Governor Mark Gordon
tweet: I did not make this decision rashly or lightly– vital state and economic interests are at stake. This case is about the right of states to conduct commerce, a question as old as our Constitution.
